<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB06450</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT IMPOSING A MORATORIUM ON THE OPEN PIT METHOD OF MINING FOR COPPER, GOLD, SILVER, AND COMPLEX ORES IN THE PHILIPPINES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : “ Open Pit Mining Moratorium Act ”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Provides for a 25-year moratorium or suspension on the approval and commencement of mining projects which covers all existing approved and pending mining projects that have not commenced commercial operation.
Intends to craft a National Industrialization Program (NIP) and a Mineral Management Plan (MMP) as a precondition to the consideration of the feasibility of open-pit mining method after a mandatory review of this Act after twelve (12) years.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ZARATE, CARLOS ISAGANI T., BROSAS, ARLENE D., CASTRO, FRANCE L., ELAGO, SARAH JANE I.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2020-03-03</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON NATURAL RESOURCES ON 2020-03-09</td></tr></table>